{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the answers from the model may \"overfit\" on the specific activity sets, especially when there is a one-to-one mapping between activities in the set and sensor events.We will explore whether the flexibility of pre-trained LLMs can also be effective in open-world HAR, where there is no fixed set of activities to consider.",
    "One of the main challenges will be that the LLM may provide different labels for the same activity (e.g., eating may also be recognized as dining, snacking, having lunch, etc.).",
    "Hence, we believe that in such settings it will be necessary to semantically cluster the predicted labels.",
    "Cloud vs Local LLM processingIn our experiments, we adopted cloud-based LLM models due to their effectiveness and to simplify the implementation.",
    "However, outsourcing information about personal activities to such untrusted third parties raises several privacy concerns."
  ]
}